d when loading the ExposedNonceAndIv class, but according to the JLS, class initialization only happens when it's first actively used. Also, I note that loading the test class doesn’t initialize nested classes or their superclasses, which should be okay. There’s also a thought about BouncyCastle potentially checking a thread-local override instead of the System properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9KyPmVnGguDoeZdnn3iCdgl3|fc_0b36a48590bbef99016a2681279c0881958009c78b19370986", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"class Properties\" -n /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/main/extracted/org/bouncycastle/util/Properties.java && grep -n \"getPropertyValue\\|isOverrideSet\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/main/extracted/org/bouncycastle/util/Properties.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2519, "output": 973, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42404, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780908301840, "responseId": "resp_0b36a48590bbef99016a26810e81c88195bb463346528809a3"}}
